  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> From a technical point of view, I thing BEM classes should be defined in the widget, and then passed to the React component. This will let us share some components (like refinementList) but still allow them to have different classes (ais-toggle and ais-menu instead of all having `ais-refinement-list).\n\nLet's go to be able to configure the whole BEM classes, we will see if it's well used or not later on, no big deal. We just need to make sure that we document the widgets options with some priorization. From most used features to least.\n",
